THE Senior Special Assistant to the President on Micro Small and Medium Enterprises MSMEs, Tola Johnson,  has said that the office of the Vice President has over the years supported the growth of small businesses across the country. According to Johnson, the VP office has been empowering and rewarding excellence in the MSME space in Nigeria The MSME clinic programme which is operational in the 30 states of the federation has been very impactful. The SSA to the President said ten outstanding MSMEs in different categories would receive ten cars and other prizes at the fifth edition of the National MSMEs awards which will be held on the 27th June 2022, during the World MSME Day.   Buhari approves appointment of new Statistician-General of…     Foreign airlines should engage indigenous cabin, technical…     FG orders NAICOM to enforce compulsory insurance for MDAs   The SSA disclosed this during a press briefing for the upcoming world MSME Day in Abuja while stating that a lot of businesses had benefited from the  MSME clinic one-stop shop, its share facility initiative, and the National MSMEs Awards. According to him, the maiden edition was held in Aba  Abia State in 2017. Since then it has been held in 30 states of the federation with the VP attending 28 of them. The categories for this year’s awards include the MSME Award of Excellence in Agriculture, MSME Award of Excellence in Beauty, Wellness and Cosmetics, MSME Award of Excellence in Creative Arts, and MSME Award of Excellence in Fashion and Style, MSME Award of Excellence in Leather Works. MSME Award of Excellence in Furniture and Woodwork, MSME Award of Excellence in Manufacturing  MSME Award of Excellence in Tech and innovation-driven Enterprise. Johnson assured that interested MSMEs are invited to visit the website and fill out their applications. The Portal will open for applications by 11:59 pm today, Thursday 19th May 2022 and will close on Sunday 12th June 2022.